Police spokesperson, Donald Mdhluli speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Attorney and former EFF secretary-general Godrich Gardee's daughter's body has been found abandoned outside Mbombela. Hillary Gardee was last seen on Friday, at a supermarket in Mbombela. She was with a three-year-old child who was found roaming in town at the time of her disappearance. A R100,000 reward for information has been offered. The EFF has described Hilary as an enthusiastic, kind and loving individual. She was studying IT while running her own business at the time of her death. EFF Statement On The Passing Of Hillary Gardee, Daughter Of Former Eff Secretary General Godrich Gardee pic.twitter.com/P2ZIK7RZIS Hillary Gardee was last seen on Friday, at a supermarket in Mbombela. Courtesy of #DStv403